= ZWAR Archive 2.0+
This is the web application for Zwangsarbeit-Archiv 2.0.

== Application Setup
1. generate the database.yml and setup the databases (<tt>rake db:create</tt> or <tt>rake db:create:all</tt>)
2. run the migrations: <tt>rake db:migrate</tt>
3. import the data: <tt>rake data:setup</tt>

If you need to import the data partially or via the individual steps, the last part
breaks down into these tasks:
a) <tt>rake import:metadata ./db/import_files/interviews.csv</tt>
b) <tt>rake import:tapes ./db/import_files/tapes.csv</tt>
c) <tt>rake import:segments ./db/import_files/segments.csv</tt> (this might take a while)

== Solr Setup and Indexing
Try to start the Solr server in the Jetty container by running:
<tt>rake sunspot:solr:start</tt>

There is no output on either success or failure, but checking for a solr process will give
some info:
<tt>ps ax | grep solr</tt>

In case of problems, there's a test rake task for starting up the Solr server with STDERR output:
<tt>rake solr:start</tt>

When the Solr server is running, you can index the data:
<tt>rake solr:reindex</tt>